<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="184" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1452,1706,1948]" pageId="4" pageNumber="184">
Huber worked in Herbarium MG where his collection is kept, along with duplicates in other herbaria (
<bibRefCitation author="Stafleu, F. A. &amp; Cowan, R. S." pageId="4" pageNumber="184" refId="ref8497" refString="Stafleu, F. A. &amp; Cowan, R. S. (1976 - 1988) Taxonomic Literature: A selective guide to botanical publications and collections with dates, commentaries and types, 2 nd ed., Smithsonian Libraries, last updated 28 Jun. 2012. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 48631" type="book" year="1976">Stafleu &amp; Cowan 1976</bibRefCitation>
–1988: 353). In the protologue of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="1898" box="[656,795,1742,1768]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Luehea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="4" pageNumber="184" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="parvifolia">
<emphasis box="[656,795,1742,1768]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="184">L. parvifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
only the 
<emphasis box="[900,1032,1742,1768]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="184">Guedes 576</emphasis>
collection is cited without specifying an herbarium, but we found specimens in G and RB. Therefore, according to Art. 9.3 of the ICN, we designate herein 
<emphasis box="[136,270,1814,1840]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="184">Guedes 576</emphasis>
(RB00436823) as the 
<typeStatus box="[526,629,1814,1840]" pageId="4" pageNumber="184">lectotype</typeStatus>
by choosing the most representative specimen among the traced original material and one that also best represents the protologue’s description. Based on the type materials, the application of the name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="1898" box="[280,421,1886,1912]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Luehea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="4" pageNumber="184" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="parvifolia">
<emphasis box="[280,421,1886,1912]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="184">L. parvifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is confirmed as a heterotypic synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Martius" authorityYear="1826" box="[911,1062,1886,1912]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Luehea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="4" pageNumber="184" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="paniculata">
<emphasis box="[911,1062,1886,1912]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="184">L. paniculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as previously accepted by 
<bibRefCitation author="Ducke, A." pageId="4" pageNumber="184" pagination="208 - 210" refId="ref7464" refString="Ducke, A. (1922) Tiliaceae. Arch. Jard. Bot. Rio de Janeiro 3: 208 - 210." type="journal article" year="1922">Ducke (1922)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
